casebody.data:
Sergiu TABIRTA, respondent,
v.
James J. CUMMINGS, Indv., et al., petitioners. No. 123344 Supreme Court of Illinois. May 30, 2018

Petition for Leave to Appeal Denied.

In the exercise of this Court's supervisory authority, the Appellate Court, First District, is directed to vacate its order in Tabirta v. Cummings, case No. 1-17-2891 (02/05/2018), denying the Rule 306(a)(4) petition for leave to appeal. The appellate court is directed to allow the petition for leave to appeal.
